ABC-Trans is one of Vietnam’s most recognized logistic transportation companies,
serving major department stores and supermarkets around the country. As the company
expands, it faces growing pressure to modernize its operations. Currently, many of ABC-
Trans’s processes—such as vehicle management, driver management, customer order
processing, shipment tracking, and payments—are either manual or handled using
disconnected branch-specific systems. These limitations result in slow service, frequent
service unavailability, customer dissatisfaction, and operational inefficiencies that
hinder the company’s potential for scaling further.
To overcome these challenges, ABC-Trans has decided to develop a centralized Smart
Fleet Management System (SmartFM). SmartFM is expected to transform the way the
company manages customers, vehicles, shipments and the related operations across
all of its branches. The system will enable customers to engage with ABC-Trans both in-
branch and through online web site and mobile app. Customers must be able to browse
and search for vehicle and shipment offerings, verify their availability at specific
locations, place orders conveniently, receive invoices and make payments. The system
is also required to produce basic statistics about shipments and resource utilisation over
various periods (a day, a week, a month, a year, or year to date) etc.
The system should help staff track and process incoming orders efficiently, approve
vehicle assignments, and organize delivery and pickup options with minimum delays. To
streamline transactions, ABC-Trans needs to support multiple payment methods
(including cash, credit/debit cards, etc.), while automatically generating receipts for
both customers and internal records. In parallel, the system should provide real-time
shipment tracking to provide visibility for both the company and its customers. Accurate
and up-to-date vehicle and driver information across all branches will be critical to
reducing errors and ensuring customer satisfaction.
ABC-Trans has also expressed the desire for the system to be able to support other
features, such as discounts, loyalty programs etc. However, they have also stated that
